The paper deals with iterative coding systems and their ability to achieve capacity, which is a topic closely related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the construction of capacity-achieving degree distributions, which is a topic in network information theory (cs.NI). The perfect matching condition is a concept that is relevant to both coding theory and graph theory, which could place the paper in the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
